# RAG Pipeline Rules

## Ingestion (Trigger.dev background job)
Flow: Upload → Supabase Storage → LlamaParse → Chunk → Voyage Embed → Pinecone upsert

Never run ingestion synchronously in an API route.
Always trigger via Trigger.dev after upload completes.

## LlamaParse
- Use 'markdown' output mode — preserves structure better than plain text
- Enable 'fast_mode' for .md and .txt — LlamaParse overhead not needed
- On parse failure: fall back to pdf-parse (basic), never silently swallow
- Validate: extracted text must be > 100 chars or flag as empty

## Chunking Strategy (section-aware, not fixed-token)

| File Type | Chunk By | Max Chunk Tokens |
|---|---|---|
| CV (PDF) | Section headers (Experience / Education / Skills / Projects / Summary) | 500 |
| Cover Letter | Single chunk | 800 |
| .md / .txt | H2 headers, then 400 tokens if no headers | 400 |
| LinkedIn export | Section (About / Experience / Education / Certifications) | 500 |
| GitHub README | One chunk per repo (title + first 300 tokens of README) | 300 |

Tag every chunk:
  { userId, sourceFile, chunkType, chunkIndex, fileType, uploadedAt, wordCount }

## Voyage AI Embeddings
Model: voyage-3 (1024 dimensions, outperforms text-embedding-3-large for retrieval)
Batch size: 64 chunks per API call (rate limit aware)
Store dimensions as vector(1024) in Supabase AND in Pinecone

Pinecone upsert format:
  { id: `${userId}-${chunkId}`, values: embedding, metadata: chunk_metadata }
  Namespace: userId (one namespace per user for isolation)

## Retrieval
Query: embed the mustHaveSkills array joined as a sentence (not the full JD — too noisy)
Search: Pinecone query, topK=20, namespace=userId, filter by chunkType
Rerank: Cohere rerank-v3.5 with job description as query → take top 8

Return structure:
  { experienceChunks, skillsChunks, projectChunks, educationChunks, matchScore }

## Match Scoring
matchScore = weighted average of cosine similarity scores:
  experience chunks × 0.5
  skills chunks × 0.3
  projects chunks × 0.2

## Pinecone Schema
Index name: hireloop-docs
Dimensions: 1024
Metric: cosine
Namespaces: one per userId
Metadata fields: sourceFile, chunkType, fileType, uploadedAt, wordCount

## Supabase Table: document_chunks
id uuid primary key
user_id uuid references auth.users not null
source_file text not null
chunk_type text not null
chunk_index integer not null
content text not null
word_count integer
pinecone_id text unique not null
file_type text not null
uploaded_at timestamptz default now()

(Embedding stored in Pinecone only — not in Supabase to avoid bloat)
